07/02/2007
BUCHAREST, Romania -- Visiting British Minister for Europe Geoff Hoon announced on Tuesday (February 6th) that his country would review its decision to restrict access to its labour markets for EU newcomers Bulgaria and Romania in one year.
His statement followed a meeting with outgoing Foreign Minister Mihai Razvan Ungureanu.
The same day, Hoon and Romanian Interior Minister Vasile Blaga announced a joint campaign against human trafficking.
(Blic, Beta - 07/02/07;
Rompres, AFP - 06/02/07)
